feeling the need to hide my pads when i give some to friends who need them, feeling scared that a boy will rummage through my bag and find them 😔 - i shouldn’t be ashamed but it’s so hard not to
This reminds me of an art piece im creating- literal same concept. A bunch of Gory scenes from tv and then one blurred out tampon that says “content too disturbing to show”
@belladrennenn
The first picture though

I don't know... Never was ashamed. But yeah...maybe initially I was scared if staining....like I would forget to live and those 3-5 days my world revolved around "peechhe kuch laga toh nahi hai na?" ....but as I joined medschool... I'm more chill abt it. And even people around me. Men have become MORE understanding than they were in school. In school it was a thrill for them to ACTUALLY see a stain. But now they've become concerned and caring. So I don't worry. I know someone will tell me....even strangers. And I know it will be out of concern.  And people don't make a huge fuss about it anymore. It's a stain. Like a stain when you drop food on your clothes. And it will GO! when you wash the clothes. Sure it's unhygienic and one must change asap but not be ASHAMED.

House I was living in, I went to the bathroom and changed my pad quickly because I had to get to work , came back that afternoon and the person, older woman, shamed me because my pad had unraveled in the can and she had seen my period blood. She had had a hysterectomy 20 years earlier, so it had to be mine.
I was slapped when my parents found out I had started using tampons because only “those kinds of girls” wore tampons. I was 15 and trying to go to a friend’s pool party. 😕
Being a boy with a period is the worse. People shouldn’t get weirded out by it but I can kinda understand why some do.
LOMAO
LMAO LOL
Oh boo hoo, let me play a song for you on the worlds smallest violin
Stop being sexist on men
@nil35h93 Lol in what world does period blood equate to semen? This might be news to you but period blood is not the result of an orgasm

@nil35h93 
And if you "go out with jizz in your pants" as you put it, did you not notice you had an orgasm? If you did and you still chose to go out like that, that's your problem my dude. Contrary to popular belief we do not choose to go out with a stain on our pants, and can't will our periods away to make ourselves or other people less uncomfortable even if we wanted to. Again this might be news to you but periods can begin at any time in a month it's not something that's 100% predictable. Even if we have pads, tampons or whatever to prevent the leak our flow is not always predictable either sometimes its too heavy and it leaks through, or sometimes we don't have access to these products depending on the circumstance.
By the same logic, women shouldn't be grossed out either if I go out with jizz in my pants.
That India stuff sounds like a them problem
